1. What is npm
- http://npmjs.com/
- for javascript
- bundle software

2. Installing Packages with npm
- npm -h // help for a command
- npm install express
- npm install http-server -g // global package installation for packages you intend to use on every project
- npm init // to create package.json file to manage dependencies
- npm install colors --save // saves this package to your dependencies
- .gitignore // type in that file "node_modules/" to ignore that file on runtime // then, type npm install to install the packages in the dependencies
- npm install mocha --save-dev // saves this package to your devDependencies // then, type npm install to install and the files will show
- NODE_ENV=production npm install // to run npm in production environment

3. Updating and Uninstalling Packages with npm
- http://semver.org/
- ^ install all version releases up to new major release (2.0)
- ~ install all patch releases up to new minor release (2.1)
- npm update // installs the latest version
- npm outdated // shows outdated packages
- npm updated http-server -g // updates a global package
- npm updated npm -g // updates the npm global package
- npm uninstall colors // uninstall from the node modules folder
- npm uninstall colors --save // uninstall from the package.json file
- npm uninstall mocha --save-dev // uninstall from dev dependencies
- npm uninstall http-server -g // uninstall global pacage from local machine
- npm // show all commands
- npm help // show help for a particular command
